<subSubSection lastPageId="2" pageId="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1802,2007]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,680]" lastPageId="2" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1910,1935]" pageId="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[767,874,1910,1934]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[767,874,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1">Ophiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having plate 
<emphasis box="[1054,1063,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1">-</emphasis>
like scales on the top of the head, two pairs of scales between the rostral and the first unpaired plate, no external forelegs, and flap-like hind limbs. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,336,1982,2006]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[151,336,1982,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1">Ophiodes luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[783,890,1982,2006]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[783,890,1982,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1">Ophiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a combination of 
<number box="[1140,1152,1983,2007]" pageId="1" value="1.0">1</number>
) a uniform striped color pattern around the body, 
<number box="[440,455,152,176]" pageId="2" value="2.0">2</number>
) an absence of black supralabial bars, 
<number box="[905,919,152,176]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
) 
<number box="[937,979,152,176]" pageId="2" value="171.0">171</number>
dorsal scales between occipital and the vent, 
<number box="[218,233,188,212]" pageId="2" value="4.0">4</number>
) 
<number box="[254,282,188,212]" pageId="2" value="29.0">29</number>
scales around midbody, and 
<number box="[634,648,188,213]" pageId="2" value="5.0">5</number>
) a hind limb four scales long (
<tableCitation box="[1028,1117,188,213]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,239,1398,1421]" captionTargetBox="[159,1405,1513,1866]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Pholidosis of Ophiodes. Boldface italics indicates species where the ranges of scale counts overlap the counts in O. luciae sp. nov. Data for species other than O. luciae from Gallardo (1966) and Borges-Martins (1998) and from examined specimens." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DBD56624FFC5FFB54C89FAC3347F43A5" pageId="2" tableUuid="DBD56624FFC5FFB54C89FAC3347F43A5">
Table 
<number box="[1104,1117,188,212]" pageId="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1334,188,212]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[1147,1334,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its coloration of faint homogeneous stripes can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1094,224,248]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[924,1094,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[924,947,224,247]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. intermedius
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with its distinct broad, dark, lateral stripes, and often narrow vertebral stripe (
<figureCitation box="[710,779,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1071,1093]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal pattern of Paraguayan species of Ophiodes: A— O. intermedius (MNHNP 6969), B: O. fragilis (MNHNP 9036), C: O. striatus (MNHNP 11341), D: Ophiodes sp “ 3 ” (MNHNP 7628)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238537/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[764,779,260,284]" pageId="2" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A); from 
<taxonomicName box="[887,1044,260,284]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vertebralis">
<emphasis box="[887,1044,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[887,910,260,283]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. vertebralis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with its distinct dorsolateral dark and light stripes, from 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[409,525,296,320]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Seps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[409,525,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[409,432,296,319]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. fragilis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its broad dark and pale lateral lines (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1073,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1071,1093]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal pattern of Paraguayan species of Ophiodes: A— O. intermedius (MNHNP 6969), B: O. fragilis (MNHNP 9036), C: O. striatus (MNHNP 11341), D: Ophiodes sp “ 3 ” (MNHNP 7628)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238537/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1057,1073,296,320]" pageId="2" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B); and from 
<taxonomicName box="[1225,1344,296,319]" class="Reptilia" family="Pygopodidae" genus="Pygopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis box="[1225,1344,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1248,296,319]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. striatus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its well-defined light and dark body stripes (
<figureCitation box="[626,696,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1071,1093]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal pattern of Paraguayan species of Ophiodes: A— O. intermedius (MNHNP 6969), B: O. fragilis (MNHNP 9036), C: O. striatus (MNHNP 11341), D: Ophiodes sp “ 3 ” (MNHNP 7628)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238537/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[680,696,332,356]" pageId="2" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Like 
<taxonomicName box="[798,904,332,356]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[798,904,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[798,821,332,355]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. luciae
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[919,1026,332,356]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[919,1026,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. “ 
<number box="[1090,1101,332,356]" pageId="2" value="1.0">1</number>
” has a series of narrow dark lines on the body and tail, but the stripes are darker and much more obvious in the latter; 
<taxonomicName box="[1173,1280,368,392]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1173,1280,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. “ 
<number box="[1341,1356,368,392]" pageId="2" value="2.0">2</number>
” has 
<number box="[1422,1436,368,392]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
well-marked dorsolateral dark lines, the second broader than the other two; and 
<taxonomicName box="[1040,1147,404,428]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1040,1147,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. “ 
<number box="[1204,1218,404,428]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
” has a broad olivebrown middorsal stripe that occupies three scale rows, and 
<number box="[814,828,440,464]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
narrower dark and light dorsolateral stripes (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1401,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1071,1093]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Dorsal pattern of Paraguayan species of Ophiodes: A— O. intermedius (MNHNP 6969), B: O. fragilis (MNHNP 9036), C: O. striatus (MNHNP 11341), D: Ophiodes sp “ 3 ” (MNHNP 7628)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238537/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1401,440,464]" pageId="2" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D). 
<taxonomicName box="[151,338,476,500]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[151,338,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the distinct black bars that are on the faces of all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1069,1176,476,500]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1176,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName box="[1270,1428,476,500]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vertebralis">
<emphasis box="[1270,1428,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[1270,1293,476,499]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. vertebralis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,336,512,536]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[151,336,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="2">Ophiodes luciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is stouter than 
<taxonomicName box="[515,684,512,536]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[515,684,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[515,538,512,535]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. intermedius
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[742,907,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<taxonomicName box="[742,903,512,536]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vertebralis">
<collectingCountry box="[742,765,512,535]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. vertebralis
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The posterior limb flap of 
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1328,512,536]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="luciae">
<emphasis box="[1223,1328,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1246,512,535]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. luciae
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[1345,1360,512,536]" pageId="2" value="4.0">4</number>
scales long) is shorter than that of 
<taxonomicName box="[466,633,548,572]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Ophiodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[466,633,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="2">
<collectingCountry box="[466,489,548,571]" name="Iceland" pageId="2">O</collectingCountry>
. intermedius
</emphasis>
